sourceMeaningMnemonic: You dig <radical>nine</radical> <radical>hole</radical>s for your <kanji>research</kanji>. You should always do research with nine variables so you can compare them and so there's an uneven number.
meaningInfo: Imagine carefully digging nine holes so you can do your research. Hmm, I wonder what kind of research these holes are for...
readingInfo: Put nine full grown cucumbers into their holes so you can research what happens next.
